12169 #
12170 def DoImpedance():
12171 
12172 # Input Variables
12173  global PeakdbA, PeakdbB, PeakRelPhase, PeakdbAB
12174  #(VZ/VA)from vector voltmeter
12175  # global VVangle # angle in degrees between VZ and VA
12176  global RsystemEntry # resistance of series resistor or power divider
12177 # Computed outputs
12178  # global VVangleCosine # cosine of vector voltmeter angle
12179  global ImpedanceMagnitude # in ohms
12180  global ImpedanceAngle # in degrees
12181  global ImpedanceRseries, ImpedanceXseries # in ohms
12182  global IA_Ext_Conf
12183 
12184  DEG2RAD = (math.pi / 180.0)
12185  SMALL = 1E-20
12186  try:
12187  ResValue = float(RsystemEntry.get())
12188  except:
12189  ResValue = 1000.0
12190 
12191  VA = math.pow(10,(PeakdbA/20))
12192  VB = math.pow(10,(PeakdbB/20))
12193  VVangleCosine = math.cos(math.radians(PeakRelPhase))
12194  if IA_Ext_Conf.get() == 1:
12195  VAB = math.pow(10,(PeakdbAB/20))
12196  VZ = VAB # VZ=VA-VB
12197  # VI = VB
12198  else:
12199  VZ = VB # VZ=VB
12200  VI = math.sqrt(VA**2 + VZ**2 - 2*VA*VZ*VVangleCosine)
12201  costheta = (VA**2 + VI**2 - VZ**2)/(2 * VA * VI)
12202  Za = ResValue * VA / VI
12203  ImpedanceRseries = Za * costheta - ResValue
12204  ImpedanceMagnitude = ResValue * VZ / VI
12205  ImpedanceXseries = math.sqrt(ImpedanceMagnitude**2 - ImpedanceRseries**2)
12206 
12207  if(PeakRelPhase < 0.0):
12208  ImpedanceXseries = -ImpedanceXseries
12209  if IA_Ext_Conf.get() == 1:
12210  ImpedanceRseries = -ImpedanceRseries
12211  ImpedanceAngle = math.atan2(ImpedanceXseries, ImpedanceRseries) / DEG2RAD
12212 #
12213 def MakeIATrace(): # Update the grid and trace
12214  global FFTmemoryA, FFTresultA, FFTresultAB, PhaseAB
12215  global FFTmemoryB, FFTresultB
12216  global PhaseA, PhaseB, PhaseMemoryA, PhaseMemoryB
12217  global PeakxA, PeakyA, PeakxB, PeakyB, PeakdbA, PeakdbB, PeakRelPhase, PeakdbAB
12218  global PeakxM, PeakyM, PeakMdb, PeakfreqM, PeakphaseA, PeakphaseB
12219  global PeakfreqA, PeakfreqB, GainCorEntry, PhaseCorEntry, PhaseCorrection
12220  global DBdivindex # Index value
12221  global DBdivlist # dB per division list
12222  global DBlevel # Reference level
12223  global GRHIA # Screenheight
12224  global GRWIA # Screenwidth
12225  global AWGSAMPLErate, SAMPLErate, BaseSampleRate
12226  global STARTsample, STOPsample, LoopNum, FSweepMode
12227  global TRACEmode, Two_X_Sample, IA_Ext_Conf
12228  global T1Vline, T2Vline, TMline, T1Pline, T2Pline
12229  global Vdiv # Number of vertical divisions
12230  global X0LIA # Left top X value
12231  global Y0TIA # Left top Y value
12232  global ImpedanceMagnitude # in ohms
12233  global ImpedanceAngle # in degrees
12234  global ImpedanceRseries, ImpedanceXseries # in ohms
12235 
12236  # Set the TRACEsize variable
12237  TRACEsize = len(FFTresultA) # Set the trace length
12238  Fsample = float(SAMPLErate / 2) / (TRACEsize - 1)
12239  # Horizontal conversion factors (frequency Hz) and border limits
12240  STARTsample = 0 # First sample in FFTresult[] that is used
12241  STARTsample = int(math.ceil(STARTsample)) # First within screen range
12242  if Two_X_Sample.get() == 0:
12243  STOPsample = 45000 / Fsample # Last sample in FFTresult[] that is used
12244  else:
12245  STOPsample = 90000 / Fsample
12246  STOPsample = int(math.floor(STOPsample)) # Last within screen range, math.floor actually not necessary, part of int
12247 #
12248  try:
12249  GainCorrection = float(eval(GainCorEntry.get()))
12250  except:
12251  GainCorEntry.delete(0,END)
12252  GainCorEntry.insert(0, GainCorrection)
12253 
12254  try:
12255  PhaseCorrection = float(eval(PhaseCorEntry.get()))
12256  except:
12257  PhaseCorEntry.delete(0,END)
12258  PhaseCorEntry.insert(0, PhaseCorrection)
12259 
12260  MAXsample = TRACEsize # Just an out of range check
12261  if STARTsample > (MAXsample - 1):
12262  STARTsample = MAXsample - 1
12263 
12264  if STOPsample > MAXsample:
12265  STOPsample = MAXsample
12266 
12267  n = STARTsample
12268  PeakfreqA = PeakfreqB = PeakfreqM = F = n * Fsample
12269  PeakphaseA = PhaseA[n]
12270  PeakphaseB = PhaseB[n]
12271  #PeakphaseAB = PhaseAB[n]
12272  PeakSample = n
12273 
12274  PeakdbA = (10 * math.log10(float(FFTresultA[n])) + 17)
12275  PeakdbB = (10 * math.log10(float(FFTresultB[n])) + 17)
12276  PeakMdb = PeakdbA - PeakdbB
12277  if IA_Ext_Conf.get() == 1:
12278  PeakdbAB = (10 * math.log10(float(FFTresultAB[n])) + 17)
12279  while n <= STOPsample:
12280  F = n * Fsample
12281  try:
12282  dbA = (10 * math.log10(float(FFTresultA[n])) + 17) # Convert power to DBs, except for log(0) error
12283  except:
12284  dbA = -200
12285  if dbA > PeakdbA:
12286  PeakdbA = dbA
12287  PeakfreqA = F
12288  PeakphaseA = PhaseA[n]
12289  PeakSample = n
12290 
12291  try:
12292  dbB = (10 * math.log10(float(FFTresultB[n])) + 17) # Add 17 dB for max value of +10 dB ALSO in CSV file routine!
12293  except:
12294  dbB = -200
12295  if dbB > PeakdbB:
12296  PeakdbB = dbB
12297  PeakfreqB = F
12298  PeakphaseB = PhaseB[n]
12299 
12300  if IA_Ext_Conf.get() == 1:
12301  try:
12302  dbAB = (10 * math.log10(float(FFTresultAB[n])) + 17) # Add 17 dB for max value of +10 dB ALSO in CSV file routine!
12303  except:
12304  dbAB = -200
12305  if dbAB > PeakdbAB:
12306  PeakdbAB = dbAB
12307  PeakphaseAB = PhaseAB[n]
12308  RelPhase = PhaseA[n]-PhaseB[n]
12309  if RelPhase > 180:
12310  RelPhase = RelPhase - 360
12311  elif RelPhase < -180:
12312  RelPhase = RelPhase + 360
12313  if Two_X_Sample.get() == 0:
12314  PhErr = 0.0018 * n * Fsample # calculate pahse error due half sample period offset
12315  RelPhase = RelPhase + PhErr - 12.0
12316  else:
12317  RelPhase = RelPhase - 9.0
12318  n = n + 1
12319  if IA_Ext_Conf.get() == 1:
12320  PeakRelPhase = PeakphaseAB-PeakphaseA
12321  else:
12322  PeakRelPhase = PeakphaseB-PeakphaseA
12323 #
12324  if PeakRelPhase > 180:
12325  PeakRelPhase = PeakRelPhase - 360
12326  elif PeakRelPhase < -180:
12327  PeakRelPhase = PeakRelPhase + 360
12328  if Two_X_Sample.get() == 0:
12329  PhErr = 0.0018 * PeakSample * Fsample # calculate pahse error due half sample period offset
12330  PeakRelPhase = PeakRelPhase + PhaseCorrection - PhErr # - 12
12331  else:
12332  PeakRelPhase = PeakRelPhase + PhaseCorrection
12333  PeakdbB = PeakdbB + GainCorrection
12334  DoImpedance()
12335

12401  x = TRadius*math.cos(RAngle)

12555  IAca.create_text (x, y, text=txt, anchor=W, fill=COLORtext, font=("arial", FontSize+4 ))
12556  y = y + 20
12557  txt = "Resistance" + ' {0:.1f} '.format(Rparallel) + "ohms"
12558  IAca.create_text (x, y, text=txt, anchor=W, fill=COLORtext, font=("arial", FontSize+4 ))
12559  y = y + 20
12560  dissp = abs(ImpedanceRseries/ImpedanceXseries) * 100 # Dissipation factor is ratio of XR to XC in percent
12561  txt = 'D = {0:.2f} '.format(dissp) + " %"
12562  IAca.create_text (x, y, text=txt, anchor=W, fill=COLORtext, font=("arial", FontSize+4 ))
12563 
12564  elif ImpedanceXseries > 0: # calculate series inductance
12565  y = y + 24
12566  try:
12567  Lseries = ImpedanceXseries / ( 2 * 3.14159 * PeakfreqA ) # in henry
12568  except:
12569  Lseries = 0
12570  Qseries = (2*math.pi*PeakfreqA*Lseries)/ImpedanceRseries
12571  Lparallel = Lseries * ((1+Qseries**2) / Qseries**2)
12572  Lparallel = Lparallel * 1E3 # convert to millihenry
12573  Rparallel = ImpedanceRseries * (1+Qseries**2)
12574  Lseries = Lseries * 1E3 # in millihenry
12575  if DisplaySeries.get() == 0:
12576  txt = "Series Inductance"
12577  IAca.create_text (x, y, text=txt, anchor=W, fill=COLORtext, font=("arial", FontSize+4 ))
12578  y = y + 22
12579  if Lseries < 1:
12580  Lseries = Lseries * 1E3
12581  txt = ' {0:.2f} '.format(Lseries) + "uH"
12582  else:
12583  txt = ' {0:.2f} '.format(Lseries) + "mH"
12584  IAca.create_text(x, y, text=txt, anchor=W, fill=COLORtext, font=("arial", FontSize+4 ))
12585  else:
12586  txt = "Parallel"
12587  IAca.create_text (x, y, text=txt, anchor=W, fill=COLORtext, font=("arial", FontSize+4 ))
12588  y = y + 20
12589  if Lparallel < 1:
12590  Lparallel = Lparallel * 1E3
12591  txt = "Inductance " + ' {0:.2f} '.format(Lparallel) + "uH"
12592  else:
12593  txt = "Inductance " + ' {0:.2f} '.format(Lparallel) + "mH"
12594  IAca.create_text(x, y, text=txt, anchor=W, fill=COLORtext, font=("arial", FontSize+4 ))
12595  y = y + 20
12596  txt = "Resistance" + ' {0:.1f} '.format(Rparallel) + "ohms"
12597  IAca.create_text (x, y, text=txt, anchor=W, fill=COLORtext, font=("arial", FontSize+4 ))
12598  y = y + 20
12599  qf = abs(ImpedanceXseries/ImpedanceRseries) * 100 # Quality Factor is ratio of XL to XR
12600  txt = 'Q = {0:.2f} '.format(qf)
12601  IAca.create_text (x, y, text=txt, anchor=W, fill=COLORtext, font=("arial", FontSize+4 ))
12602  # Start and stop frequency and trace mode
12603  if Two_X_Sample.get() == 0:
12604  txt = "0.0 to 45000 Hz"
12605  else:
12606  txt = "0.0 to 90000 Hz"
12607  txt = txt + " FFT Bandwidth =" + ' {0:.2f} '.format(FFTbandwidth)
12608 
12609  x = X0LIA
12610  y = Y0TIA+GRHIA-13
12611  idTXT = IAca.create_text (x, y, text=txt, anchor=W, fill=COLORtext)
12612  txt = " "
12613  if FreqTraceMode.get() == 1:
12614  txt ="Normal mode "
12615 
12616  if FreqTraceMode.get() == 2:
12617  txt = "Peak hold mode "
12618 
12619  if FreqTraceMode.get() == 3:
12620  txt = "Power average mode (" + str(TRACEaverage.get()) + ") "
12621 
12622  if ZEROstuffing.get() > 0:
12623  txt = txt + "Zero Stuffing = " + str(ZEROstuffing.get())
12624  # Runstatus and level information
12625  if (RUNstatus.get() == 0):
12626  txt = txt + " Stopped "
12627  else:
12628  txt = txt + " Running "
12629  y = Y0TIA+GRHIA
12630  IDtxt = IAca.create_text (x, y, text=txt, anchor=W, fill=COLORtext)

12841 def NqPCaresize(event):
12842  global NqPca, GRWNqP, XOLNqP, GRHNqP, Y0TNqP, CANVASwidthNqP, CANVASheightNqP, FontSize
12843 
12844  CANVASwidthNqP = event.width - 4
12845  CANVASheightNqP = event.height - 4
12846  GRWNqP = CANVASwidthNqP - (2 * X0LNqP) # new grid width
12847  GRHNqP = CANVASheightNqP - Y0TNqP - int(1.25 * FontSize) # 10 new grid height
12848  UpdateNqPAll()
12849 #
12850 def MakeNqPScreen():
12851  global NqPca, GRWNqP, XOLNqP, GRHNqP, Y0TNqP, CANVASwidthNqP, CANVASheightNqP, COLORtrace1
12852  global COLORgrid, GridWidth, SmoothCurvesBP, SmoothBool, DBlevelBP, DBdivlist, DBdivindexBP
12853  global FSweepAdB, FSweepBdB, FSweepBPh, FSweepAPh, ShowMathBP, NqPline, Two_X_Sample, TRACEwidth
12854  global Vdiv, FBins, FStep
12855  global FontSize
12856 
12857  de = NqPca.find_enclosed( -10000, -10000, CANVASwidthNqP+10000, CANVASheightNqP+10000 )
12858  # Delete all items on the canvas
12859  for n in de:
12860  NqPca.delete(n)
12861  SmoothBool = SmoothCurvesBP.get()
12862  # Draw circular grid lines
12863  i = 1
12864  xcenter = GRWNqP/2
12865  ycenter = GRHNqP/2
12866  Radius = (GRWNqP-X0LNqP)/(1 + Vdiv.get() * 2) # 11
12867  dBperPixel = float(DBdivlist[DBdivindexBP.get()])/Radius
12868  TRadius = Radius * Vdiv.get() # 5
12869  x1 = X0LNqP
12870  x2 = X0LNqP + GRWNqP
12871  xright = 10 + xcenter + ( Vdiv.get() * Radius ) # 5
12872  while (i <= Vdiv.get()):
12873  x0 = xcenter - ( i * Radius )
12874  x1 = xcenter + ( i * Radius )
12875  y0 = ycenter - ( i * Radius )
12876  y1 = ycenter + ( i * Radius )
12877  dBaxis_value = (DBlevelBP.get() - (i * DBdivlist[DBdivindexBP.get()]))
12878  NqPca.create_oval ( x0, y0, x1, y1, outline=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get())
12879  NqPca.create_line(xcenter, y0, xright, y0, fill=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get(), dash=(4,3))
12880  NqPca.create_text(xright, y0, text=str(dBaxis_value), fill=COLORgrid, anchor="w", font=("arial", FontSize+2 ))
12881  #
12882  i = i + 1
12883  NqPca.create_line(xcenter, y0, xcenter, y1, fill=COLORgrid, width=2)
12884  NqPca.create_line(x0, ycenter, x1, ycenter, fill=COLORgrid, width=2)
12885  RAngle = math.radians(45)
12886  y = TRadius*math.sin(RAngle)
12887  x = TRadius*math.cos(RAngle)
12888  NqPca.create_line(xcenter-x, ycenter-y, xcenter+x, ycenter+y, fill=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get())
12889  NqPca.create_line(xcenter+x, ycenter-y, xcenter-x, ycenter+y, fill=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get())
12890  NqPca.create_text(x0, ycenter, text="180", fill=COLORgrid, anchor="e", font=("arial", FontSize+2 ))
12891  NqPca.create_text(x1, ycenter, text="0.0", fill=COLORgrid, anchor="w", font=("arial", FontSize+2 ))
12892  NqPca.create_text(xcenter, y0, text="90", fill=COLORgrid, anchor="s", font=("arial", FontSize+2 ))
12893  NqPca.create_text(xcenter, y1, text="-90", fill=COLORgrid, anchor="n", font=("arial", FontSize+2 ))
12894  # xcenter = xcenter + (DBlevelBP.get()/dBperPixel)
12895 # Draw traces
12896  NqPline = []
12897  if len(FSweepAdB) > 4:
12898  for index in range(len(FSweepAdB)): # while n < len(FStep):
12899  if index < len(FStep): # check if n has gone out off bounds because user did something dumb
12900  F = FBins[int(FStep[index])] # look up frequency bin in list of bins
12901  else:
12902  F = FBins[int(FStep[0])]
12903  # Mag value
12904  dbA = (10 * math.log10(float(FSweepAdB[index])) + 17) # Convert power to DBs, except for log(0) error
12905  dbB = (10 * math.log10(float(FSweepBdB[index])) + 17) # Add 17 dB for max value of +10 dB ALSO in CSV file routine!
12906  if ShowMathBP.get() == 1:
12907  MdB = dbA - dbB
12908  elif ShowMathBP.get() == 2:
12909  MdB = dbB - dbA
12910  MagRadius = (-MdB / dBperPixel) + (DBlevelBP.get()/dBperPixel)
12911  # Phase Value
12912  RelPhase = FSweepBPh[index] - FSweepAPh[index]
12913  if RelPhase > 180:
12914  RelPhase = RelPhase - 360
12915  elif RelPhase < -180:
12916  RelPhase = RelPhase + 360
12917  if Two_X_Sample.get() == 0:
12918  PhErr = 0.0018 * F # calculate phase error due half sample period offset
12919  RelPhase = RelPhase - PhErr # - PhaseOffset1x # - 12.0
12920  else:
12921  RelPhase = RelPhase # - PhaseOffset2x # - 9.0
12922  y1 = ycenter - MagRadius*math.sin(math.radians(RelPhase))
12923  if y1 > 1500:
12924  y1 = xright
12925  elif y1 < -500:
12926  y1 = ycenter - xright
12927  x1 = xcenter + MagRadius*math.cos(math.radians(RelPhase ))
12928  if x1 > 1500:
12929  x1 = xright
12930  elif x1 < -500:
12931  x1 = xcenter - xright
12932  NqPline.append(x1)
12933  NqPline.append(y1)
12934  NqPca.create_line(NqPline, fill=COLORtrace1, smooth=SmoothBool, splinestep=5, width=TRACEwidth.get())
12935 #

12979 def MakeNiCScreen():
12980  global NiCline, NiCca, CANVASwidthNic, CANVASheightNic, X0LNiC, GRWNiC, Y0TNiC, GRHNiC, X0TNiC
12981  global COLORzeroline, GridWidth, COLORgrid, FSweepAdB, FSweepBdB, Two_X_Sample, ShowMathBP
12982  global FSweepBPh, FSweepAPh, SmoothCurvesBP, SmoothBool, DBlevelBP, DBdivlist, DBdivindexBP
12983  global Vdiv, FBins, FStep, PhCenBodeEntry, RelPhaseCenter
12984  global FontSize
12985 
12986  Ymin = Y0TNiC # Minimum position of XY grid (top)
12987  Ymax = Y0TNiC + GRHNiC # Maximum position of XY grid (bottom)
12988  Xmin = X0LNiC # Minimum position of XY grid (left)
12989  Xmax = X0LNiC + GRWNiC # Maximum position of XY grid (right)
12990  try:
12991  Phasecenter = int(PhCenBodeEntry.get())
12992  RelPhaseCenter.set(Phasecenter)
12993  except:
12994  PhCenBodeEntry.delete(0,"end")
12995  PhCenBodeEntry.insert(0,0)
12996  RelPhaseCenter.set(0)
12997  Phasecenter = 0
12998  # Delete all items on the screen
12999  de = NiCca.find_enclosed( -1000, -1000, CANVASwidthNic+1000, CANVASheightNic+1000)
13000  MarkerNum = 0
13001  SmoothBool = SmoothCurvesBP.get()
13002  for n in de:
13003  NiCca.delete(n)
13004  # Draw horizontal grid lines Rel Gain Magnitude
13005  i = 0
13006  x1 = X0LNiC
13007  x2 = X0TNiC = X0LNiC + GRWNiC
13008  mg_siz = GRWNiC/10.0
13009  mg_inc = mg_siz/5.0
13010  DegPerDiv = 360 / 10
13011  while (i < Vdiv.get()+1):
13012  dBaxis_value = (DBlevelBP.get() - (i * DBdivlist[DBdivindexBP.get()]))
13013  y = Y0TNiC + i * GRHNiC/Vdiv.get()
13014  Dline = [x1,y,x2,y]
13015  if dBaxis_value == 0:
13016  NiCca.create_line(Dline, fill=COLORzeroline, width=GridWidth.get()) # Blue line at center of grid
13017  k = 0
13018  while (k < 10):
13019  l = 1
13020  while (l < 5): # add tick marks
13021  Dline = [x1+k*mg_siz+l*mg_inc,y-5,x1+k*mg_siz+l*mg_inc,y+5]
13022  NiCca.create_line(Dline, fill=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get())
13023  l = l + 1
13024  k = k + 1
13025  else:
13026  NiCca.create_line(Dline, fill=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get())
13027  dBaxis_label = str(dBaxis_value)
13028  NiCca.create_text(x1-3, y, text=dBaxis_label, fill=COLORtrace1, anchor="e", font=("arial", FontSize ))
13029 
13030  i = i + 1
13031  # Draw vertical grid lines (phase -180 to 180 10 div)
13032  i = 0
13033  y1 = Y0TNiC
13034  y2 = Y0TNiC + GRHNiC
13035  mg_siz = GRHNiC/10.0
13036  mg_inc = mg_siz/5.0
13037  #
13038  while (i < 11):
13039  x = X0LNiC + i * GRWNiC/10.0
13040  Dline = [x,y1,x,y2]
13041  axis_value = Phasecenter - 180 + (i * DegPerDiv)
13042  axis_label = str(axis_value)
13043  if ( axis_value == 0):
13044  NiCca.create_line(Dline, fill=COLORzeroline, width=GridWidth.get()) # Blue vertical line at center of grid
13045  k = 0
13046  while (k < 10):
13047  l = 1
13048  while (l < 5): # add tick marks
13049  Dline = [x-5,y1+k*mg_siz+l*mg_inc,x+5,y1+k*mg_siz+l*mg_inc]
13050  NiCca.create_line(Dline, fill=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get())
13051  l = l + 1
13052  k = k + 1
13053  else:
13054  NiCca.create_line(Dline, fill=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get())
13055  NiCca.create_text(x, y2+3, text=axis_label, fill=COLORtrace3, anchor="n", font=("arial", FontSize ))
13056  i = i + 1
13057  # Draw traces
13058  # Vertical conversion factors (level dBs) and border limits
13059  Yconv = float(GRHNiC) / (Vdiv.get() * DBdivlist[DBdivindexBP.get()]) # Conversion factors, Yconv is the number of screenpoints per dB
13060  Yc = float(Y0TNiC) + Yconv * (DBlevelBP.get()) # Yc is the 0 dBm position, can be outside the screen!
13061  Xphconv = float(GRWNiC / 360.0) # degrees per pixel
13062  Xp = float(X0LNiC) + Xphconv * 180.0
13063  x1 = X0LNiC + 14
13064  # Horizontal conversion factors (phase deg) and border limits
13065  NiCline = []
13066  if len(FSweepAdB) > 4:
13067  index = 0
13068  for index in range(len(FSweepAdB)): # while n < len(FStep):
13069  if index < len(FStep): # check if n has gone out off bounds because user did something dumb
13070  F = FBins[int(FStep[index])] # look up frequency bin in list of bins
13071  else:
13072  F = FBins[int(FStep[0])]
13073  # Mag value
13074  dbA = (10 * math.log10(float(FSweepAdB[index])) + 17) # Convert power to DBs, except for log(0) error
13075  dbB = (10 * math.log10(float(FSweepBdB[index])) + 17) # Add 17 dB for max value of +10 dB ALSO in CSV file routine!
13076  if ShowMathBP.get() == 1:
13077  MdB = dbA - dbB
13078  elif ShowMathBP.get() == 2:
13079  MdB = dbB - dbA
13080  yb = Yc - Yconv * MdB
13081  if (yb < Ymin):
13082  yb = Ymin
13083  if (yb > Ymax):
13084  yb = Ymax
13085  # Phase Value
13086  RelPhase = FSweepBPh[index] - FSweepAPh[index]
13087  RelPhase = RelPhase - Phasecenter
13088  if RelPhase > 180:
13089  RelPhase = RelPhase - 360
13090  elif RelPhase < -180:
13091  RelPhase = RelPhase + 360
13092  if Two_X_Sample.get() == 0:
13093  PhErr = 0.0018 * F # calculate phase error due half sample period offset
13094  RelPhase = RelPhase - PhErr # - PhaseOffset1x # - 12.0
13095  else:
13096  RelPhase = RelPhase # - PhaseOffset2x
13097  xa = Xp + Xphconv * RelPhase
13098  if (xa < Xmin):
13099  xa = Ymin
13100  if (xa > Xmax):
13101  xa = Xmax
13102  NiCline.append(int(xa + 0.5))
13103  NiCline.append(int(yb + 0.5))
13104  NiCca.create_line(NiCline, fill=COLORtrace1, smooth=SmoothBool, splinestep=5, width=TRACEwidth.get())

13144 def STOREcsvfile(): # Store the trace as CSV file [frequency, magnitude or dB value]
13145  global FFTmemoryA, FFTresultA
13146  global FFTmemoryB, FFTresultB
13147  global PhaseA, PhaseB, freqwindow
13148  global AWGSAMPLErate, SAMPLErate, BaseSampleRate, ShowC1_VdB, ShowC2_VdB
13149 
13150  # Set the TRACEsize variable
13151  if ShowC1_VdB.get() == 1:
13152  TRACEsize = len(FFTresultA) # Set the trace length
13153  elif ShowC2_VdB.get() == 1:
13154  TRACEsize = len(FFTresultB)
13155  if TRACEsize == 0: # If no trace, skip rest of this routine
13156  return()
13157 # ask if save as magnitude or dB
13158  dB = askyesno("Mag or dB: ","Save amplidude data as dB (Yes) or Mag (No):\n", parent=freqwindow)
13159  # Make the file name and open it
13160  tme = strftime("%Y%b%d-%H%M%S", gmtime()) # The time
13161  filename = "Spectrum-" + tme
13162  filename = filename + ".csv"
13163  # open file to save data
13164  filename = asksaveasfilename(initialfile = filename, defaultextension = ".csv",
13165  filetypes=[("Comma Separated Values", "*.csv")], parent=freqwindow)
13166  DataFile = open(filename,'a') # Open output file
13167  HeaderString = 'Frequency-#, '
13168  if ShowC1_VdB.get() == 1:
13169  if dB == 1:
13170  HeaderString = HeaderString + 'CA-dB, '
13171  if dB == 0:
13172  HeaderString = HeaderString + 'CA-Mag, '
13173  if ShowC2_VdB.get() == 1:
13174  if dB == 1:
13175  HeaderString = HeaderString + 'CB-dB, '
13176  if dB == 0:
13177  HeaderString = HeaderString + 'CB-Mag, '
13178  if ShowC1_P.get() == 1:
13179  HeaderString = HeaderString + 'Phase A-B, '
13180  if ShowC2_P.get() == 1:
13181  HeaderString = HeaderString + 'Phase B-A, '
13182  HeaderString = HeaderString + '\n'
13183  DataFile.write( HeaderString )
13184 
13185  Fsample = float(SAMPLErate / 2) / (TRACEsize - 1) # Frequency step per sample
13186 
13187  n = 0
13188  while n < TRACEsize:
13189  F = n * Fsample
13190  txt = str(F)
13191  if ShowC1_VdB.get() == 1:
13192  V = 10 * math.log10(float(FFTresultA[n])) + 17 # Add 17 dB for max value of +10 dB
13193  if dB == 0:
13194  V = 10.0**(V/20.0)
13195  txt = txt + "," + str(V)
13196  if ShowC2_VdB.get() == 1:
13197  V = 10 * math.log10(float(FFTresultB[n])) + 17 # Add 17 dB for max value of +10 dB
13198  if dB == 0:
13199  V = 10.0**(V/20.0)
13200  txt = txt + "," + str(V)
13201  if ShowC1_P.get() == 1:
13202  RelPhase = PhaseA[n]-PhaseB[n]
13203  if RelPhase > 180:
13204  RelPhase = RelPhase - 360
13205  elif RelPhase < -180:
13206  RelPhase = RelPhase + 360
13207  txt = txt + "," + str(RelPhase)
13208  if ShowC2_P.get() == 1:
13209  RelPhase = PhaseB[n]-PhaseA[n]
13210  if RelPhase > 180:
13211  RelPhase = RelPhase - 360
13212  elif RelPhase < -180:
13213  RelPhase = RelPhase + 360
13214  txt = txt + "," + str(RelPhase)
13215  txt = txt + "\n"
13216  DataFile.write(txt)
13217  n = n + 1
13218 
13219  DataFile.close() # Close the file

13221 def MakeFreqScreen(): # Update the screen with traces and text
13222  global CANVASheightF, CANVASwidthF, SmoothCurvesSA
13223  global PeakxA, PeakyA, PeakxB, PeakyB, PeakdbA, PeakdbB
13224  global PeakxM, PeakyM, PeakMdb, PeakfreqM
13225  global PeakfreqA, PeakfreqB, PeakfreqRA, PeakfreqRB
13226  global PeakxRA, PeakyRA, PeakxRB, PeakyRB, PeakdbRA, PeakdbRB
13227  global PeakxRM, PeakyRM, PeakRMdb, PeakfreqRM, PeakIndexA, PeakIndexB, Fsample

13230  global COLORtrace1, COLORtrace2
13231  global FSweepMode, LoopNum, MarkerFreqNum, TRACEwidth, GridWidth
13232  global DBdivindex # Index value
13233  global DBdivlist # dB per division list
13234  global DBlevel # Reference level
13235  global FFTwindow, FFTbandwidth, ZEROstuffing, FFTwindowname
13236  global X0LF # Left top X value
13237  global Y0TF # Left top Y value
13238  global GRWF # Screenwidth
13239  global GRHF # Screenheight
13240  global FontSize
13241  global RUNstatus # 0 stopped, 1 start, 2 running, 3 stop now, 4 stop and restart
13242  global AWGSAMPLErate, SAMPLErate, BaseSampleRate, SingleShotSA, HScale, HarmonicMarkers
13243  global SMPfft # number of FFT samples
13244  global StartFreqEntry, StopFreqEntry, PhCenFreqEntry, RelPhaseCenter
13245  global ShowC1_P, ShowC2_P, ShowRA_VdB, ShowRB_VdB, ShowMarker
13246  global ShowRA_P, ShowRB_P, ShowMathSA, FreqDisp
13247  global ShowFCur, ShowdBCur, FCursor, dBCursor
13248  global T1Fline, T2Fline, T1Pline, T1FRline, T2FRline, TFMline, TFRMline
13249  global T1PRline, T2PRline
13250  global TRACEaverage # Number of traces for averageing
13251  global FreqTraceMode # 1 normal 2 max 3 average
13252  global Vdiv # Number of vertical divisions
13253 
13254  # Delete all items on the screen
13255  de = Freqca.find_enclosed( -1000, -1000, CANVASwidthF+1000, CANVASheightF+1000 )
13256  MarkerFreqNum = 0
13257  for n in de:
13258  Freqca.delete(n)
13259  try:
13260  StartFrequency = float(StartFreqEntry.get())
13261  except:
13262  StartFreqEntry.delete(0,"end")
13263  StartFreqEntry.insert(0,100)
13264  StartFrequency = 100
13265  try:
13266  StopFrequency = float(StopFreqEntry.get())
13267  except:
13268  StopFreqEntry.delete(0,"end")
13269  StopFreqEntry.insert(0,10000)
13270  StopFrequency = 10000
13271  try:
13272  Phasecenter = int(PhCenFreqEntry.get())
13273  RelPhaseCenter.set(Phasecenter)
13274  except:
13275  PhCenFreqEntry.delete(0,"end")
13276  PhCenFreqEntry.insert(0,0)
13277  RelPhaseCenter.set(0)
13278  Phasecenter = 0
13279  # Draw horizontal grid lines
13280  i = 0
13281  x1 = X0LF
13282  x2 = X0LF + GRWF
13283  while (i <= Vdiv.get()):
13284  y = Y0TF + i * GRHF/Vdiv.get()
13285  Dline = [x1,y,x2,y]
13286  if i == 0 or i == Vdiv.get():
13287  Freqca.create_line(Dline, fill=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get())
13288  else:
13289  Freqca.create_line(Dline, dash=(4,3), fill=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get())
13290  Vaxis_value = (DBlevel.get() - (i * DBdivlist[DBdivindex.get()]))
13291  Vaxis_label = str(Vaxis_value)
13292  Freqca.create_text(x1-3, y, text=Vaxis_label, fill=COLORtrace1, anchor="e", font=("arial", FontSize ))
13293  if ShowC1_P.get() == 1 or ShowC2_P.get() == 1:
13294  Vaxis_value = ( 180 - ( i * (360 / Vdiv.get())))
13295  Vaxis_value = Vaxis_value + Phasecenter
13296  Vaxis_label = str(Vaxis_value)
13297  Freqca.create_text(x2+3, y, text=Vaxis_label, fill=COLORtrace3, anchor="w", font=("arial", FontSize ))
13298  i = i + 1
13299  # Draw vertical grid lines
13300  i = 0
13301  y1 = Y0TF
13302  y2 = Y0TF + GRHF
13303  if HScale.get() == 1:
13304  F = 1.0
13305  LogFStop = math.log10(StopFrequency)
13306  try:
13307  LogFStart = math.log10(StartFrequency)
13308  except:
13309  LogFStart = 0.0
13310  LogFpixel = (LogFStop - LogFStart) / GRWF
13311  # draw left and right edges
13312  while F <= StopFrequency:
13313  if F >= StartFrequency:
13314  try:
13315  LogF = math.log10(F) # convet to log Freq
13316  x = X0LF + (LogF - LogFStart)/LogFpixel
13317  except:
13318  x = X0LF
13319  Dline = [x,y1,x,y2]
13320  if F == 1 or F == 10 or F == 100 or F == 1000 or F == 10000 or F == 100000:
13321  Freqca.create_line(Dline, fill=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get())
13322  axis_label = str(F)
13323  Freqca.create_text(x, y2+3, text=axis_label, fill=COLORgrid, anchor="n", font=("arial", FontSize ))
13324  else:
13325  Freqca.create_line(Dline, dash=(4,3), fill=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get())
13326 
13327  if F < 10:
13328  F = F + 1
13329  elif F < 100:
13330  F = F + 10
13331  elif F < 1000:
13332  F = F + 100
13333  elif F < 1000:
13334  F = F + 100
13335  elif F < 10000:
13336  F = F + 1000
13337  elif F < 100000:
13338  F = F + 10000
13339  elif F < 200000:
13340  F = F + 10000
13341  else:
13342  Freqdiv = (StopFrequency - StartFrequency) / 10
13343  while (i < 11):
13344  x = X0LF + i * GRWF/10.0
13345  Dline = [x,y1,x,y2]
13346  if i == 0 or i == 10:
13347  Freqca.create_line(Dline, fill=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get())
13348  else:
13349  Freqca.create_line(Dline, dash=(4,3), fill=COLORgrid, width=GridWidth.get())
13350  axis_value = (StartFrequency + (i * Freqdiv))
13351  axis_label = str(axis_value)
13352  Freqca.create_text(x, y2+3, text=axis_label, fill=COLORgrid, anchor="n", font=("arial", FontSize ))
13353  i = i + 1
13354  # Draw X - Y cursors if needed
13355  Yconv = float(GRHF) / (Vdiv.get() * DBdivlist[DBdivindex.get()]) # Conversion factors, Yconv is the number of screenpoints per dB
13356  Yc = float(Y0TF) + Yconv * (DBlevel.get()) # Yc is the 0 dBm position, can be outside the screen!
13357  Fpixel = (StopFrequency - StartFrequency) / GRWF # Frequency step per screen pixel
13358  if ShowFCur.get() > 0:
13359  Dline = [FCursor, Y0TF, FCursor, Y0TF+GRHF]
13360  Freqca.create_line(Dline, dash=(3,4), fill=COLORtrigger, width=GridWidth.get())
13361  # Horizontal conversion factors (frequency Hz) and border limits
13362  if HScale.get() == 1:
13363  LogFStop = math.log10(StopFrequency)
13364  try:
13365  LogFStart = math.log10(StartFrequency)
13366  except:
13367  LogFStart = 0.0
13368  LogFpixel = (LogFStop - LogFStart) / GRWF
13369  xfreq = 10**(((FCursor-X0LF)*LogFpixel) + LogFStart)
13370  else:
13371  Fpixel = (StopFrequency - StartFrequency) / GRWF # Frequency step per screen pixel
13372  xfreq = ((FCursor-X0LF)*Fpixel)+StartFrequency
13373  XFString = ' {0:.2f} '.format(xfreq)
13374  V_label = XFString + " Hz"
13375  Freqca.create_text(FCursor+1, dBCursor-5, text=V_label, fill=COLORtext, anchor="w", font=("arial", FontSize ))
13376 #
13377  if ShowdBCur.get() > 0:
13378  Dline = [X0LF, dBCursor, X0LF+GRWF, dBCursor]
13379  Freqca.create_line(Dline, dash=(3,4), fill=COLORtrigger, width=GridWidth.get())
13380  # Vertical conversion factors (level dBs) and border limits
13381  Yconv = float(GRHF) / (Vdiv.get() * DBdivlist[DBdivindex.get()]) # Conversion factors, Yconv is the number of screenpoints per dB
13382  Yc = float(Y0TF) + Yconv * (DBlevel.get()) # Yc is the 0 dBm position, can be outside the screen!
13383  yvdB = ((Yc-dBCursor)/Yconv)
13384  VdBString = ' {0:.1f} '.format(yvdB)
13385  V_label = VdBString + " dBV"
13386  Freqca.create_text(FCursor+1, dBCursor+5, text=V_label, fill=COLORtext, anchor="w", font=("arial", FontSize ))
13387  #
13388  SmoothBool = SmoothCurvesSA.get()
13389  # Draw traces
13390  if len(T1Fline) > 4: # Avoid writing lines with 1 coordinate
13391  # Write the trace CHA
13392  if OverRangeFlagA == 1:
13393  Freqca.create_line(T1Fline, fill=COLORsignalband, smooth=SmoothBool, splinestep=5, width=TRACEwidth.get())
13394  else:
13395  Freqca.create_line(T1Fline, fill=COLORtrace1, smooth=SmoothBool, splinestep=5, width=TRACEwidth.get())
13396  if ShowMarker.get() > 0:
13397  k = 1
13398  while k <= HarmonicMarkers.get():
13399  try:
13400  dbA = (10 * math.log10(float(FFTresultA[PeakIndexA*k])) + 17)
13401  FreqA = k*PeakIndexA*Fsample
13402  if ShowMarker.get() == 2 and k > 1:
13403  Peak_label = ' {0:.2f} '.format(dbA - PeakdbA) + ',' + ' {0:.1f} '.format(FreqA - PeakfreqA)
13404  else:
13405  Peak_label = ' {0:.2f} '.format(dbA) + ',' + ' {0:.1f} '.format(FreqA)
13406  if HScale.get() == 1:
13407  try:
13408  LogF = math.log10(FreqA) # convet to log Freq
13409  xA = X0LF + int((LogF - LogFStart)/LogFpixel)
13410  except:
13411  xA = X0LF
13412  else:
13413  xA = X0LF+int((FreqA - StartFrequency)/Fpixel)# +StartFrequency
13414  yA = Yc - Yconv * dbA
13415  Freqca.create_text(xA, yA, text=Peak_label, fill=COLORtrace1, anchor="s", font=("arial", FontSize ))
13416  k = k + 1
13417  except:
13418  k = k + 1
13419  if len(T2Fline) > 4: # Avoid writing lines with 1 coordinate
13420  # Write the trace CHB
13421  if OverRangeFlagB == 1:
13422  Freqca.create_line(T2Fline, fill=COLORsignalband, smooth=SmoothBool, splinestep=5, width=TRACEwidth.get())
13423  else:
13424  Freqca.create_line(T2Fline, fill=COLORtrace2, smooth=SmoothBool, splinestep=5, width=TRACEwidth.get())
13425  if ShowMarker.get() > 0:
13426  k = 1
13427  while k <= HarmonicMarkers.get():
13428  try:
13429  dbB = (10 * math.log10(float(FFTresultB[PeakIndexB*k])) + 17)
13430  FreqB = k*PeakIndexB*Fsample
13431  if ShowMarker.get() == 2 and k > 1:
13432  Peak_label = ' {0:.2f} '.format(dbB - PeakdbB) + ',' + ' {0:.1f} '.format(FreqB - PeakfreqB)
13433  else:
13434  Peak_label = ' {0:.2f} '.format(dbB) + ',' + ' {0:.1f} '.format(FreqB)
13435  if HScale.get() == 1:
13436  try:
13437  LogF = math.log10(FreqB) # convet to log Freq
13438  xB = X0LF + int((LogF - LogFStart)/LogFpixel)
13439  except:
13440  xB = X0LF
13441  else:
13442  xB = X0LF+int((FreqB - StartFrequency)/Fpixel)# +StartFrequency
13443  yB = Yc - Yconv * dbB
13444  Freqca.create_text(xB, yB, text=Peak_label, fill=COLORtrace2, anchor="s", font=("arial", FontSize ))
13445  k = k + 1
13446  except:
13447  k = k + 1
13448  if len(T1Pline) > 4: # Avoid writing lines with 1 coordinate
13449  # Write the phase trace A-B
13450  Freqca.create_line(T1Pline, fill=COLORtrace3, smooth=SmoothBool, splinestep=5, width=TRACEwidth.get())
13451  if len(T2Pline) > 4: # Avoid writing lines with 1 coordinate
13452  # Write the phase trace A-B
13453  Freqca.create_line(T2Pline, fill=COLORtrace4, smooth=SmoothBool, splinestep=5, width=TRACEwidth.get())
13454  if ShowRA_VdB.get() == 1 and len(T1FRline) > 4: # Write the ref trace A if active
13455  Freqca.create_line(T1FRline, fill=COLORtraceR1, smooth=SmoothBool, splinestep=5, width=TRACEwidth.get())
13456  if ShowMarker.get() == 1:
13457  Peak_label = ' {0:.2f} '.format(PeakdbRA) + ',' + ' {0:.1f} '.format(PeakfreqRA)
13458  Freqca.create_text(PeakxRA, PeakyRA, text=Peak_label, fill=COLORtraceR1, anchor="s", font=("arial", FontSize ))
13459  if ShowRB_VdB.get() == 1 and len(T2FRline) > 4: # Write the ref trace B if active
13460  Freqca.create_line(T2FRline, fill=COLORtraceR2, smooth=SmoothBool, splinestep=5, width=TRACEwidth.get())
13461  if ShowMarker.get() == 1:

13463  Freqca.create_text(PeakxRB, PeakyRB, text=Peak_label, fill=COLORtraceR2, anchor="s", font=("arial", FontSize ))

13497

13527 def INITIALIZEstart():
13528  global SMPfft, FFTwindow
13529  global SMPfftpwrTwo, BodeDisp
13530  global TRACEresetFreq, FreqTraceMode, LoopNum, FSweepMode, FSweepCont
13531 
13532  # First some subroutines to set specific variables
13533  if BodeDisp.get() == 0:
13534  if FFTwindow.get() != 8:
13535  SMPfft = 2 ** int(SMPfftpwrTwo.get()) # Calculate the number of FFT samples from SMPfftpwrtwo
13536 
13537  CALCFFTwindowshape()
13538  if FreqTraceMode.get() == 1 and TRACEresetFreq == False:
13539  TRACEresetFreq = True # Clear the memory for averaging or peak
13540  if FreqTraceMode.get() == 2 and LoopNum.get() == 1 and FSweepMode.get() > 0 and FSweepCont.get() == 0 and BodeDisp.get() >0:
13541  TRACEresetFreq = True # Clear the memory for peak hold when using sweep generator
13542 
13543 def CALCFFTwindowshape(): # Make the FFTwindowshape for the windowing function
13544  global FFTbandwidth # The FFT bandwidth
13545  global FFTwindow # Which FFT window number is selected
13546  global FFTwindowname # The name of the FFT window function
13547  global FFTwindowshape # The window shape
13548  global AWGSAMPLErate, SAMPLErate, BaseSampleRate # The sample rate
13549  global SMPfft # Number of FFT samples
13550  global LastWindow, LastSMPfft
13551 
13552  if LastWindow == FFTwindow.get() and LastSMPfft == SMPfft:
13553  # recalculate window only if something changed
13554  return
13555  # FFTname and FFTbandwidth in milliHz
13556  FFTwindowname = "No such window"
13557  FFTbw = 0
13558 
13559  if FFTwindow.get() == 0:
13560  FFTwindowname = " Rectangular (no) window (B=1) "
13561  FFTbw = 1.0
13562 
13563  if FFTwindow.get() == 1:
13564  FFTwindowname = " Cosine window (B=1.24) "
13565  FFTbw = 1.24
13566 
13567  if FFTwindow.get() == 2:
13568  FFTwindowname = " Triangular window (B=1.33) "
13569  FFTbw = 1.33
13570 
13571  if FFTwindow.get() == 3:
13572  FFTwindowname = " Hann window (B=1.5) "
13573  FFTbw = 1.5
13574 
13575  if FFTwindow.get() == 4:
13576  FFTwindowname = " Blackman window (B=1.73) "
13577  FFTbw = 1.73
13578 
13579  if FFTwindow.get() == 5:
13580  FFTwindowname = " Nuttall window (B=2.02) "
13581  FFTbw = 2.02
13582 
13583  if FFTwindow.get() == 6:
13584  FFTwindowname = " Flat top window (B=3.77) "
13585  FFTbw = 3.77
13586 
13587  if FFTwindow.get() == 7:
13588  FFTwindowname = FFTUserWindowString
13589  FFTbw = 0.0
13590  try:
13591  FFTwindowshape = eval(FFTUserWindowString)
13592  except:
13593  FFTwindowshape = numpy.ones(SMPfft) # Initialize with ones
13594  print "Filling FFT window with Ones"
13595  elif FFTwindow.get() == 8: # window shape array read from csv file
13596  FFTwindowname = "Window Shape From file"
13597  FFTbw = 0.0
13598  else:
13599  FFTbandwidth = int(FFTbw * SAMPLErate / float(SMPfft))
13600  # Calculate the shape
13601  FFTwindowshape = numpy.ones(SMPfft) # Initialize with ones
13602  n = 0
13603  while n < SMPfft:
13604  # Cosine window function - medium-dynamic range B=1.24
13605  if FFTwindow.get() == 1:
13606  w = math.sin(math.pi * n / (SMPfft - 1))
13607  FFTwindowshape[n] = w * 1.571
13608  # Triangular non-zero endpoints - medium-dynamic range B=1.33
13609  if FFTwindow.get() == 2:
13610  w = (2.0 / SMPfft) * ((SMPfft/ 2.0) - abs(n - (SMPfft - 1) / 2.0))
13611  FFTwindowshape[n] = w * 2.0
13612  # Hann window function - medium-dynamic range B=1.5
13613  if FFTwindow.get() == 3:
13614  w = 0.5 - 0.5 * math.cos(2 * math.pi * n / (SMPfft - 1))
13615  FFTwindowshape[n] = w * 2.000
13616  # Blackman window, continuous first derivate function - medium-dynamic range B=1.73
13617  if FFTwindow.get() == 4:
13618  w = 0.42 - 0.5 * math.cos(2 * math.pi * n / (SMPfft - 1)) + 0.08 * math.cos(4 * math.pi * n / (SMPfft - 1))
13619  FFTwindowshape[n] = w * 2.381
13620  # Nuttall window, continuous first derivate function - high-dynamic range B=2.02
13621  if FFTwindow.get() == 5:
13622  w = 0.355768 - 0.487396 * math.cos(2 * math.pi * n / (SMPfft - 1)) + 0.144232 * math.cos(4 * math.pi * n / (SMPfft - 1))- 0.012604 * math.cos(6 * math.pi * n / (SMPfft - 1))
13623  FFTwindowshape[n] = w * 2.811
13624  # Flat top window, medium-dynamic range, extra wide bandwidth B=3.77
13625  if FFTwindow.get() == 6:
13626  w = 1.0 - 1.93 * math.cos(2 * math.pi * n / (SMPfft - 1)) + 1.29 * math.cos(4 * math.pi * n / (SMPfft - 1))- 0.388 * math.cos(6 * math.pi * n / (SMPfft - 1)) + 0.032 * math.cos(8 * math.pi * n / (SMPfft - 1))
13627  FFTwindowshape[n] = w * 1.000
13628  n = n + 1
13629  LastWindow = FFTwindow.get()
13630  LastSMPfft = SMPfft
13631 
13632 def BUserFFTwindow():
13633  global FFTUserWindowString, freqwindow
13634 
13635  TempString = FFTUserWindowString
13636  FFTUserWindowString = askstring("User FFT Window", "Current User Window: " + FFTUserWindowString + "\n\nNew Window:\n", initialvalue=FFTUserWindowString, parent=freqwindow)
13637  if (FFTUserWindowString == None): # If Cancel pressed, then None
13638  FFTUserWindowString = TempString

13640 def BFileFFTwindow():
13641  global FFTwindowshape, SMPfft, LastSMPfft, FFTwindow, LastWindow
13642 
13643  # Read values from CVS file
13644  filename = askopenfilename(defaultextension = ".csv", filetypes=[("CSV files", "*.csv")], parent=freqwindow)
13645  try:
13646  CSVFile = open(filename)
13647  csv_f = csv.reader(CSVFile)
13648  FFTwindowshape = []
13649  for row in csv_f:
13650  try:
13651  FFTwindowshape.append(float(row[0]))
13652  except:
13653  print 'skipping non-numeric row'
13654  FFTwindowshape = numpy.array(FFTwindowshape)
13655  CSVFile.close()
13656  SMPfft = len(FFTwindowshape)
13657  LastSMPfft = SMPfft
13658  LastWindow = FFTwindow.get()
13659  print SMPfft
13660  except:
13661  showwarning("WARNING","No such file found or wrong format!")

13683 def onCanvasFreqLeftClick(event):
13684  global X0LF # Left top X value
13685  global Y0TF # Left top Y value
13686  global GRWF # Screenwidth
13687  global GRHF # Screenheight
13688  global FontSize
13689  global Freqca, MarkerLoc, SAMPLErate, BaseSampleRate
13690  global COLORgrid, COLORtext, HScale, ShowC1_VdB, ShowC2_VdB
13691  global COLORtrace1, COLORtrace2, StartFreqEntry, StopFreqEntry
13692  global AWGSAMPLErate, RUNstatus, COLORtext, MarkerFreqNum, PrevdBV, PrevF
13693 
13694  if (RUNstatus.get() == 0):
13695  MarkerFreqNum = MarkerFreqNum + 1
13696  COLORmarker = COLORgrid
13697  if ShowC1_VdB.get() == 1:
13698  COLORmarker = COLORtrace1
13699  elif ShowC2_VdB.get() == 1:
13700  COLORmarker = COLORtrace2
13701  try:
13702  StartFrequency = float(StartFreqEntry.get())
13703  except:
13704  StartFreqEntry.delete(0,"end")
13705  StartFreqEntry.insert(0,100)
13706  StartFrequency = 100
13707  try:
13708  StopFrequency = float(StopFreqEntry.get())
13709  except:
13710  StopFreqEntry.delete(0,"end")
13711  StopFreqEntry.insert(0,100)
13712  StopFrequency = 100
13713  # draw X at marker point and number
13714  Freqca.create_line(event.x-4, event.y-4,event.x+4, event.y+5, fill=COLORmarker)
13715  Freqca.create_line(event.x+4, event.y-4,event.x-4, event.y+5, fill=COLORmarker)
13716  Freqca.create_text(event.x+4, event.y, text=str(MarkerFreqNum), fill=COLORmarker, anchor="w", font=("arial", FontSize ))
13717  # Vertical conversion factors (level dBs) and border limits
13718  Yconv = float(GRHF) / (Vdiv.get() * DBdivlist[DBdivindex.get()]) # Conversion factors, Yconv is the number of screenpoints per dB
13719  Yc = float(Y0TF) + Yconv * (DBlevel.get()) # Yc is the 0 dBm position, can be outside the screen!
13720  Yphconv = float(GRHF) / 360
13721  Yp = float(Y0TF) + Yphconv + 180
13722  # Horizontal conversion factors (frequency Hz) and border limits
13723  if HScale.get() == 1:
13724  LogFStop = math.log10(StopFrequency)
13725  try:
13726  LogFStart = math.log10(StartFrequency)
13727  except:
13728  LogFStart = 0.0
13729  LogFpixel = (LogFStop - LogFStart) / GRWF
13730  xfreq = 10**(((event.x-X0LF)*LogFpixel) + LogFStart)
13731  else:
13732  Fpixel = (StopFrequency - StartFrequency) / GRWF # Frequency step per screen pixel
13733  xfreq = ((event.x-X0LF)*Fpixel)+StartFrequency
13734 
13735  yvdB = ((Yc-event.y)/Yconv)
13736  VdBString = ' {0:.1f} '.format(yvdB)
13737  XFString = ' {0:.2f} '.format(xfreq)
13738  V_label = str(MarkerFreqNum) + " " + XFString + " Hz, " + VdBString + " dBV"
13739  if MarkerFreqNum > 1:
13740  DeltaV = ' {0:.3f} '.format(yvdB-PrevdBV)
13741  DeltaF = ' {0:.2f} '.format(xfreq-PrevF)
13742  V_label = V_label + " Delta " + DeltaF + " Hz, " + DeltaV + " dBV"
13743  x = X0LF + 5
13744  y = Y0TF + 3 + (MarkerFreqNum*10)
13745  Justify = 'w'
13746  if MarkerLoc == 'UR' or MarkerLoc == 'ur':
13747  x = X0LF + GRWF - 5
13748  y = Y0TF + 3 + (MarkerFreqNum*10)
13749  Justify = 'e'
13750  if MarkerLoc == 'LL' or MarkerLoc == 'll':
13751  x = X0LF + 5
13752  y = Y0TF + GRHF + 3 - (MarkerFreqNum*10)
13753  Justify = 'w'
13754  if MarkerLoc == 'LR' or MarkerLoc == 'lr':
13755  x = X0LF + GRWF - 5
13756  y = Y0TF + GRHF + 3 - (MarkerFreqNum*10)
13757  Justify = 'e'
13758  Freqca.create_text(x, y, text=V_label, fill=COLORmarker, anchor=Justify, font=("arial", FontSize ))
13759  PrevdBV = yvdB
13760  PrevF = xfreq

13914  # Vertical conversion factors (level dBs) and border limits
13915  Yconv = float(GRHBP) / (Vdiv.get() * DBdivlist[DBdivindexBP.get()]) # Conversion factors, Yconv is the number of screenpoints per dB
13916  Yc = float(Y0TBP) + Yconv * (DBlevelBP.get()) # Yc is the 0 dBm position, can be outside the screen!
13917  Yphconv = float(GRHBP) / 360
13918  Yp = float(Y0TBP) + Yphconv + 180
13919  x1 = X0LBP + 14
13920  x2 = x1 + GRWBP
13921  # Horizontal conversion factors (frequency Hz) and border limits
13922  if HScaleBP.get() == 1:
13923  LogFStop = math.log10(EndFreq)
13924  try:
13925  LogFStart = math.log10(BeginFreq)
13926  except:
13927  LogFStart = 0.0
13928  LogFpixel = (LogFStop - LogFStart) / GRWBP
13929  xfreq = 10**(((event.x-x1)*LogFpixel) + LogFStart)
13930  else:
13931  Fpixel = (EndFreq - BeginFreq) / GRWBP # Frequency step per screen pixel
13932  xfreq = ((event.x-x1)*Fpixel)+BeginFreq
13933 
13934  yvdB = ((Yc-event.y)/Yconv)
13935  VdBString = ' {0:.1f} '.format(yvdB)
13936  XFString = ' {0:.2f} '.format(xfreq)
13937  V_label = str(MarkerFreqNum) + " " + XFString + " Hz, " + VdBString + " dBV"
13938  if MarkerFreqNum > 1:
13939  DeltaV = ' {0:.3f} '.format(yvdB-PrevdBV)
13940  DeltaF = ' {0:.2f} '.format(xfreq-PrevF)
13941  V_label = V_label + " Delta " + DeltaF + " Hz, " + DeltaV + " dBV"
13942  x = x1 + 5
13943  y = Y0TBP + 3 + (MarkerFreqNum*10)
13944  Justify = 'w'
13945  if MarkerLoc == 'UR' or MarkerLoc == 'ur':
13946  x = x2 - 5
13947  y = Y0TBP + 3 + (MarkerFreqNum*10)
13948  Justify = 'e'
13949  if MarkerLoc == 'LL' or MarkerLoc == 'll':
13950  x = x1 + 5
13951  y = Y0TBP + GRHBP + 3 - (MarkerFreqNum*10)
13952  Justify = 'w'
13953  if MarkerLoc == 'LR' or MarkerLoc == 'lr':
13954  x = x2 - 5
13955  y = Y0TBP + GRHBP + 3 - (MarkerFreqNum*10)
13956  Justify = 'e'
13957  Bodeca.create_text(x, y, text=V_label, fill=COLORmarker, anchor=Justify, font=("arial", FontSize ))
13958  PrevdBV = yvdB
13959  PrevF = xfreq

14062 def onTextScroll(event): # august 7
14063  button = event.widget
14064  cursor_position = button.index(INSERT) # get current cursor position
14065  Pos = cursor_position
14066  OldVal = button.get() # get current entry string
14067  OldValfl = float(OldVal) # and its value
14068  Len = len(OldVal)
14069  Dot = OldVal.find (".") # find decimal point position
14070  Decimals = Len - Dot - 1
14071  if Dot == -1 : # no point
14072  Decimals = 0
14073  Step = 10**(Len - Pos)
14074  elif Pos <= Dot : # no point left of position
14075  Step = 10**(Dot - Pos)
14076  else :
14077  Step = 10**(Dot - Pos + 1)
14078  if event.delta > 0: # increment value
14079  NewVal = OldValfl + Step
14080  else: # decrement value
14081  NewVal = OldValfl - Step
14082  FormatStr = "{0:." + str(Decimals) + "f}"
14083  NewStr = FormatStr.format(NewVal)
14084  NewDot = NewStr.find (".")
14085  NewPos = Pos + NewDot - Dot
14086  if Decimals == 0 :
14087  NewLen = len(NewStr)
14088  NewPos = Pos + NewLen - Len
14089  button.delete(0, END) # remove old entry
14090  button.insert(0, NewStr) # insert new entry
14091  button.icursor(NewPos) # resets the insertion cursor

14109 def onTextKey(event):
14110 
14111  button = event.widget
14112  cursor_position = button.index(INSERT) # get current cursor position
14113  NewPos = cursor_position -1
14114  OldVal = button.get() # get current entry string
14115  OldDigit = OldVal[NewPos]
14116  if platform.system() == "Windows":
14117  if event.keycode == 38: # increment digit for up arrow key
14118  NewDigit = int(OldDigit) + 1
14119  elif event.keycode == 40: # decrement digit for down arrow
14120  NewDigit = int(OldDigit) - 1
14121  else:
14122  return
14123  elif platform.system() == "Linux":
14124  if event.keycode == 111: # increment digit for up arrow key
14125  NewDigit = int(OldDigit) + 1
14126  elif event.keycode == 116: # decrement digit for down arrow
14127  NewDigit = int(OldDigit) - 1
14128  else:
14129  return
14130  if OldDigit == ".": # if cursor next to decimal point nop
14131  return
14132  if NewDigit > 9:
14133  NewDigit = 0
14134  button.delete(NewPos) # remove old digit
14135  button.insert(NewPos,NewDigit) # insert new digit
14136  NewPos = cursor_position-2
14137  if NewPos < 0:
14138  return
14139  CarryDigit = OldVal[NewPos]
14140  if CarryDigit == ".": # if carry is decimal point
14141  NewPos = cursor_position-3
14142  CarryDigit = OldVal[NewPos]
14143  NewDigit = int(CarryDigit) + 1
14144  if NewDigit > 9:
14145  NewDigit = 0
14146  button.delete(NewPos) # remove old digit
14147  button.insert(NewPos,NewDigit) # insert new digit
14148  elif NewDigit < 0:
14149  NewDigit = 9
14150  button.delete(NewPos) # remove old digit
14151  button.insert(NewPos,NewDigit) # insert new digit
14152  NewPos = cursor_position-2
14153  if NewPos < 0:
14154  return
14155  CarryDigit = OldVal[NewPos]
14156  if CarryDigit == ".": # if carry is decimal point
14157  NewPos = cursor_position-3
14158  CarryDigit = OldVal[NewPos]
14159  NewDigit = int(CarryDigit) - 1
14160  if NewDigit < 0:
14161  NewDigit = 9
14162  button.delete(NewPos) # remove old digit
14163  button.insert(NewPos,NewDigit) # insert new digit
14164  else:
14165  button.delete(NewPos) # remove old digit
14166  button.insert(NewPos,NewDigit) # insert new digit
14167 #
14168 def onSpinBoxScroll(event):
14169  spbox = event.widget
14170  if event.delta > 0: # increment digit
14171  spbox.invoke('buttonup')
14172  else: # decrement digit
14173  spbox.invoke('buttondown')

14500 def BAWG2X():
14501  global AWG_2X, devx, AWGAIOMode, AWGBIOMode, BisCompA
14502 
14503  ReMakeAWGwaves()
14504  if AWG_2X.get() == 0: # configure board for both AWG channels at 1X sampling
14505  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x24, 0x0, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set to addr DAC A
14506  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x25, 0x1, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set to addr DAC B
14507  elif AWG_2X.get() == 1: # configure board for single AWG channel A at 2X sampling
14508  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x24, 0x0, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set to addr DAC A
14509  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x25, 0x0, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set t0 addr DAC A
14510  if AWGBIOMode.get() == 0: # if channel b is not in split I/O mode turn off output
14511  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 40, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set IN3 switch to open
14512  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 52, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set IN3 switch to open
14513  BisCompA.set(0)
14514  elif AWG_2X.get() == 2: # configure board for single AWG channel B at 2X sampling
14515  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x24, 0x1, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set to addr DAC B
14516  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x25, 0x1, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set to addr DAC B
14517  if AWGAIOMode.get() == 0: # if channel a is not in split I/O mode turn off output
14518  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 35, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set IN3 switch to open
14519  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 51, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set IN3 switch to open
14520  BisCompA.set(0)

14695 def BodeCaresize(event):
14696  global Bodeca, GRWBP, XOLBP, GRHBP, Y0TBP, CANVASwidthBP, CANVASheightBP, FontSize
14697 
14698  CANVASwidthBP = event.width - 4
14699  CANVASheightBP = event.height - 4
14700  GRWBP = CANVASwidthBP - (2 * X0LBP) # new grid width
14701  GRHBP = CANVASheightBP - int(10 * FontSize) # new grid height
14702  UpdateBodeAll()

14704 def BStepSync():
14705  global FStepSync, DevOne
14706 
14707  if FStepSync.get() == 0:
14708  Tval = devx.ctrl_transfer( 0xc0, 0x91, 0, 0, 0, 1, 100) # set PIO-0 to Z
14709  elif FStepSync.get() == 1:
14710  devx.ctrl_transfer( 0x40, 0x50, 0, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set PIO-0 to 0
14711  elif FStepSync.get() == 2:
14712  devx.ctrl_transfer( 0x40, 0x51, 0, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set PIO-0 to 1
14713 #
14714 def BSweepSync():
14715  global FSweepSync, DevOne
14716 
14717  if FSweepSync.get() == 0:
14718  Tval = devx.ctrl_transfer( 0xc0, 0x91, 1, 0, 0, 1, 100) # set PIO-1 to Z
14719  elif FSweepSync.get() == 1:
14720  devx.ctrl_transfer( 0x40, 0x50, 1, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set PIO-1 to 0
14721  elif FSweepSync.get() == 2:
14722  devx.ctrl_transfer( 0x40, 0x51, 1, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set PIO-1 to 1
14723 #
14724 def BDSweepFromFile():
14725  global BDSweepFile, FileSweepFreq, FileSweepAmpl
14726 
14727  if BDSweepFile.get() > 0:
14728  # Read values from CVS file
14729  filename = askopenfilename(defaultextension = ".csv", filetypes=[("CSV files", "*.csv")], parent = bodewindow)
14730  try:
14731  CSVFile = open(filename)
14732  csv_f = csv.reader(CSVFile)
14733  FileSweepFreq = []
14734  FileSweepAmpl = []
14735  for row in csv_f:
14736  try:
14737  FileSweepFreq.append(float(row[0]))
14738  FileSweepAmpl.append(float(row[1]))
14739  except:
14740  print 'skipping non-numeric row'
14741  FileSweepFreq = numpy.array(FileSweepFreq)
14742  FileSweepAmpl = numpy.array(FileSweepAmpl)
14743  MaxAmpl = numpy.amax(FileSweepAmpl)
14744  NormAmpl = MaxAmpl
14745  s = askstring("Normalize Max Amplitude", "Max Amplitude = " + str(MaxAmpl) + "\n\n Enter New Max value:\n in dB", parent = bodewindow)
14746  if (s == None): # If Cancel pressed, then None
14747  return()
14748  try: # Error if for example no numeric characters or OK pressed without input (s = "")
14749  v = int(s)
14750  except:
14751  s = "error"
14752 
14753  if s != "error":
14754  NormAmpl = MaxAmpl - v
14755  else:
14756  NormAmpl = MaxAmpl
14757  FileSweepAmpl = FileSweepAmpl - NormAmpl # normalize max amplitude to requested dBV
14758  CSVFile.close()
14759  StopBodeEntry.delete(0,"end")
14760  StopBodeEntry.insert(0,FileSweepFreq[len(FileSweepFreq)-1])
14761  StartBodeEntry.delete(0,"end")
14762  StartBodeEntry.insert(0,FileSweepFreq[0])
14763  SweepStepBodeEntry.delete(0,"end")
14764  SweepStepBodeEntry.insert(0,len(FileSweepFreq))
14765  except:
14766  showwarning("WARNING","No such file found or wrong format!", parent = bodewindow)
14767 #

15064 def FreqCaresize(event):
15065  global Freqca, GRWF, XOLF, GRHF, Y0TF, CANVASwidthF, CANVASheightF, FontSize
15066 
15067  CANVASwidthF = event.width - 4
15068  CANVASheightF = event.height - 4
15069  GRWF = CANVASwidthF - (2 * X0LF) # new grid width
15070  GRHF = CANVASheightF - int(10 * FontSize) # new grid height
15071  UpdateFreqAll()

15314 def DestroySpectrumScreen():
15315  global freqwindow, SpectrumScreenStatus, ca
15316 
15317  SpectrumScreenStatus.set(0)
15318  FreqDisp.set(0)
15319  FreqCheckBox()
15320  freqwindow.destroy()

15322 #
15323 def XYcaresize(event):
15324  global XYca, GRWXY, XOLXY, GRHXY, Y0TXY, CANVASwidthXY, CANVASheightXY, FontSize
15325  global YminXY, YmaxXY, XminXY, XmaxXY
15326 
15327  CANVASwidthXY = event.width - 4
15328  CANVASheightXY = event.height - 4
15329  GRWXY = CANVASwidthXY - int(2.25 * FontSize) - X0LXY # 18 new grid width
15330  GRHXY = CANVASheightXY - int(10 * FontSize) # new grid height
15331  YminXY = Y0TXY # Minimum position of time grid (top)
15332  YmaxXY = Y0TXY + GRHXY # Maximum position of time grid (bottom)
15333  XminXY = X0LXY # Minimum position of time grid (left)
15334  XmaxXY = X0LXY + GRWXY # Maximum position of time grid (right)
15335  UpdateXYAll()
15336 #
15337 # ================ Make spectrum sub window ==========================
15338 def MakeXYWindow():
15339  global logo, CANVASwidthXY, CANVASheightXY, Xsignal, Ysignal, ShowRXY
15340  global XYScreenStatus, MarkerXYScale, XYca, xywindow, RevDate, SWRev, XYDisp
15341  global CHAsbxy, CHBsbxy, CHAxylab, CHBxylab, CHAVPosEntryxy, CHBVPosEntryxy
15342  global CHAIsbxy, CHBIsbxy, CHAIPosEntryxy, CHBIPosEntryxy, ScreenXYrefresh
15343  global YminXY, Y0TXY, YmaxXY, GRHXY, XminXY, X0LXY, XmaxXY, X0LXY, GRWXY, CANVASwidthXY, CANVASheightXY
15344 
15345  if XYScreenStatus.get() == 0:
15346  XYScreenStatus.set(1)
15347  XYDisp.set(1)
15348  XYCheckBox()
15349  YminXY = Y0TXY # Minimum position of XY grid (top)
15350  YmaxXY = Y0TXY + GRHXY # Maximum position of XY grid (bottom)
15351  XminXY = X0LXY # Minimum position of XY grid (left)
15352  XmaxXY = X0LXY + GRWXY # Maximum position of XY grid (right)
15353  CANVASwidthXY = GRWXY + 18 + X0LXY # The XY canvas width
15354  CANVASheightXY = GRHXY + 80 # The XY canvas height
15355  xywindow = Toplevel()
15356  xywindow.title("X-Y Plot " + SWRev + RevDate)
15357  xywindow.protocol("WM_DELETE_WINDOW", DestroyXYScreen)

15555 def SelfCalibration():

15558  # global OnBoardResAgnd, OnBoardResA25, OnBoardResBgnd, OnBoardResB25
15559  # setup cal results window

15610  # set to default mux and dac settings
15611  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x24, 0x0, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set to addr DAC A
15612  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x25, 0x1, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set to addr DAC B
15613  AWGSync.set(1)
15614  BAWGSync()
15615  if session.continuous:
15616  print "ending session"
15617  session.end()
15618  # Setup ADALM1000
15619  if askyesno("Reset Calibration", "Do You Need To Reset Default Calibration?", parent=calwindow):
15620  #print(devx.calibration)
15621  try:
15622  devx.write_calibration("calib_default.txt")
15623  #print "wrote calib_default.txt"
15624  except:
15625  filename = askopenfilename(defaultextension = ".txt", filetypes=[("Default Cal File", "*.txt")], parent=calwindow)
15626  devx.write_calibration(filename)
15627  #print(devx.calibration)
15628  #
15629  devidstr = DevID[17:31]
15630  filename = "calib" + devidstr + ".txt"
15631  if os.path.isfile(filename):
15632  if askyesno("Calibration exists", "A previous Calibration file exists. /n Do you want to load that?", parent=calwindow):
15633  devx.write_calibration(filename)
15634  #print "wrote old ", filename
15635  calwindow.destroy()
15636  return
15637  else:
15638  if askyesno("Continue?", "Continure with self calibration?", parent=calwindow):
15639  donothing()
15640  else:
15641  calwindow.destroy()
15642  return
15643  #
15644  CalFile = open(filename, "w")
15645  #
15646  CHA.mode = Mode.HI_Z # Put CHA in Hi Z mode
15647  CHB.mode = Mode.HI_Z # Put CHB in Hi Z mode
15648  devx.ctrl_transfer( 0x40, 0x50, 34, 0, 0, 0, 100) # close voltage sense loop just in case
15649  devx.ctrl_transfer( 0x40, 0x50, 39, 0, 0, 0, 100) # close voltage sense loop just in case
15650  ADsignal1 = [] # Ain signal array channel
15651  ADsignal1 = devx.get_samples(1010)
15652  # Pause whie user connects external voltage reference AD584
15653  BadData = 1
15654  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 32, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set 2.5 V switch to open
15655  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 33, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set GND switch to open

15657  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 38, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set CHB GND switch to open

15659  try:
15660  AD584act = float(RequestVRef)*1.0
15661  except:
15662  AD584act = 3.3
15663  showinfo("CONNECT","Connect External Voltage to both CHA and CHB inputs.", parent=calwindow)
15664  while (BadData): # loop till good reading
15665  # Get A and B AD584 data
15666  CHA.mode = Mode.HI_Z # Put CHA in Hi Z mode
15667  CHB.mode = Mode.HI_Z # Put CHB in Hi Z mode

15669  CHA584Raw = CHB584Raw = 0.0 # initalize measurment variable
15670  # get_samples returns a list of values for voltage [0] and current [1]
15671  for index in range(1000): # calculate average
15672  CHA584Raw += ADsignal1[index+10][0][0] # Sum for average CA voltage
15673  CHB584Raw += ADsignal1[index+10][1][0] # Sum for average CB voltage
15674 
15675  CHA584Raw = CHA584Raw / 1000.0 # calculate average
15676  CHB584Raw = CHB584Raw / 1000.0 # calculate average
15677  VString = "Extern A Volts " + ' {0:.4f} '.format(CHA584Raw) # format with 4 decimal places

15679  VString = "Extern B Volts " + ' {0:.4f} '.format(CHB584Raw) # format with 4 decimal places
15680  labelBMax.config(text = VString) # change displayed value
15681  Lower = AD584act - 0.3
15682  Upper = AD584act + 0.3
15683  if CHA584Raw < Lower or CHA584Raw > Upper or CHB584Raw < Lower or CHB584Raw > Upper:
15684  if askyesno("CONNECT","Did not get good data from Ref V check connections!\n Abort(Y) or Try again(N)", parent=calwindow):
15685  CHA.mode = Mode.HI_Z # Put CHA in Hi Z mode

15849  CHAISr0iRaw = CHAISr0iRaw / 1000.0
15850  CHBVSr0iRaw = CHBVSr0iRaw / 1000.0 # calculate average
15851  CHBISr0iRaw = CHBISr0iRaw / 1000.0
15852  VString = "CA 2.5 Src 0 I" + ' {0:.4f} '.format(CHAISr0iRaw) # format with 4 decimal places
15853  labelSIA0.config(text = VString) # change displayed value
15854  VString = "CB 2.5 Src 0 I" + ' {0:.4f} '.format(CHBISr0iRaw) # format with 4 decimal places
15855  labelSIB0.config(text = VString) # change displayed value
15856  #
15857  # Get A and B force +0.45 current data for int 50 res to 2.5 V rail
15858  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x50, 32, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set CHA 2.5 V switch to closed
15859  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 33, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set CHA GND switch to open
15860  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x50, 37, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set CHB 2.5 V switch to closed
15861  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 38, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set CHB GND switch to open
15862  CHA.mode = Mode.SIMV
15863  CHA.constant(0.045)
15864  CHB.mode = Mode.SIMV
15865  CHB.constant(0.045)
15866  ADsignal1 = devx.get_samples(1010) # get samples for dev channel A0 and B0
15867  CHAVSr100Raw = CHAISr100Raw = CHBVSr100Raw = CHBISr100Raw = 0.0 # initalize measurment variable
15868  for index in range(1000): # calculate average
15869  CHAVSr100Raw += ADsignal1[index+10][0][0] # Sum for average CA voltage
15870  CHBVSr100Raw += ADsignal1[index+10][1][0] # Sum for average CB voltage
15871  CHAISr100Raw += ADsignal1[index+10][0][1] # Sum for average CA current
15872  CHBISr100Raw += ADsignal1[index+10][1][1] # Sum for average CB current
15873 
15874  CHAVSr100Raw = CHAVSr100Raw / 1000.0 # calculate average
15875  CHAISr100Raw = CHAISr100Raw / 1000.0
15876  CHBVSr100Raw = CHBVSr100Raw / 1000.0 # calculate average
15877  CHBISr100Raw = CHBISr100Raw / 1000.0
15878  VString = "CA 50 Src +45 " + ' {0:.4f} '.format(CHAVSr100Raw) # format with 4 decimal places
15879  labelSIA.config(text = VString) # change displayed value
15880  VString = "CB 50 Src +45 " + ' {0:.4f} '.format(CHBVSr100Raw) # format with 4 decimal places
15881  labelSIB.config(text = VString) # change displayed value
15882  #
15883  # Get A and B force -0.045 current data for int 50 res to 2.5 V rail
15884  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x50, 32, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set CHA 2.5 V switch to closed
15885  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 33, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set CHA GND switch to open
15886  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x50, 37, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set CHB 2.5 V switch to closed
15887  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 38, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set CHB GND switch to open
15888  CHA.mode = Mode.SIMV
15889  CHA.constant(-0.045)
15890  CHB.mode = Mode.SIMV
15891  CHB.constant(-0.045)
15892  ADsignal1 = devx.get_samples(1010) # get samples for dev channel A0 and B0
15893  CHAVSrN45Raw = CHAISrN45Raw = CHBVSrN45Raw = CHBISrN45Raw = 0.0 # initalize measurment variable
15894  for index in range(1000): # calculate average
15895  CHAVSrN45Raw += ADsignal1[index+10][0][0] # Sum for average CA voltage
15896  CHBVSrN45Raw += ADsignal1[index+10][1][0] # Sum for average CB voltage
15897  CHAISrN45Raw += ADsignal1[index+10][0][1] # Sum for average CA current
15898  CHBISrN45Raw += ADsignal1[index+10][1][1] # Sum for average CB current
15899 
15900  CHAVSrN45Raw = CHAVSrN45Raw / 1000.0 # calculate average
15901  CHAISrN45Raw = CHAISrN45Raw / 1000.0
15902  CHBVSrN45Raw = CHBVSrN45Raw / 1000.0 # calculate average
15903  CHBISrN45Raw = CHBISrN45Raw / 1000.0
15904  VString = "CA 50 Src -45 " + ' {0:.4f} '.format(CHAVSrN45Raw) # format with 4 decimal places
15905  labelSIAN.config(text = VString) # change displayed value
15906  VString = "CB 50 Src -45 " + ' {0:.4f} '.format(CHBVSrN45Raw) # format with 4 decimal places
15907  labelSIBN.config(text = VString) # change displayed value
15908  # return all switches to open
15909  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 32, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set 2.5 V switch to open
15910  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 33, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set GND switch to open
15911  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 37, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set CHB 2.5 V switch to open
15912  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 38, 0, 0, 0, 100) # set CHB GND switch to open
15913  # Caculate voltage gain errors
15914  #
15915  CHAF25V = CHAF25vRaw * ( AD584act / CHA584Raw )
15916  CHBF25V = CHBF25vRaw * ( AD584act / CHB584Raw )
15917  #
15918  CHASr5v = CHASr5vRaw * ( AD584act / CHA584Raw ) # calculate actual voltage
15919  CHBSr5v = CHBSr5vRaw * ( AD584act / CHB584Raw ) # calculate actual voltage
15920  #
15921  CHA2p5 = CHA2p5Raw * ( AD584act / CHA584Raw )
15922  # print "calculated fixed 2.5 from CHA ", CHA2p5
15923  CHB2p5 = CHB2p5Raw * ( AD584act / CHB584Raw )
15924  # print "calculated fixed 2.5 from CHB ", CHB2p5
15925  #
15926  CHAActSrI = CHASr5v / OnBoardRes # adjust resistor value to include switch ron
15927  CHBActSrI = CHBSr5v / OnBoardRes # adjust resistor value to include switch ron
15928  #
15929  CHAActSnkI = CHASr0vRaw - CHA2p5 / OnBoardRes # adjust resistor value to include switch ron
15930  CHBActSnkI = CHBSr0vRaw - CHB2p5 / OnBoardRes # adjust resistor value to include switch ron
15931  #
15932  CHASr0i = CHAVSr0iRaw * ( AD584act / CHA584Raw )
15933  CHASr0iAct = CHASr0i / OnBoardRes # adjust resistor value to include switch ron
15934  CHASr100 = CHAVSr100Raw * ( AD584act / CHA584Raw )
15935  CHASrI100Act = (CHASr100 - CHA2p5) / OnBoardRes # adjust resistor value to include switch ron
15936  CHASrN45 = CHAVSrN45Raw * ( AD584act / CHA584Raw )
15937  CHASrIN45Act = (CHASrN45 - CHA2p5) / OnBoardRes # adjust resistor value to include switch ron
15938  #
15939  CHBSr0i = CHBVSr0iRaw * ( AD584act / CHB584Raw )
15940  CHBSr0iAct = CHBSr0i / OnBoardRes # adjust resistor value to include switch ron
15941  CHBSr100 = CHBVSr100Raw * ( AD584act / CHB584Raw )
15942  CHBSrI100Act = (CHBSr100 - CHB2p5) / OnBoardRes # adjust resistor value to include switch ron
15943  CHBSrN45 = CHBVSrN45Raw * ( AD584act / CHB584Raw )
15944  CHBSrIN45Act = (CHBSrN45 - CHB2p5) / OnBoardRes # adjust resistor value to include switch ron
15945  # Write cal factors to file
15946  #
15947  CalFile.write('# Channel A, measure V\n')
15948  CalFile.write('</>\n')
15949  CalFile.write('<0.0000, ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHAGndRaw) + '>\n')
15950  CalFile.write('<' + '{0:.4f}'.format(AD584act) + ', ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHA584Raw) + '>\n')
15951  CalFile.write('<>\n')
15952  CalFile.write('\n')
15953  #
15954  CalFile.write('# Channel A, measure I\n')
15955  CalFile.write('</>\n')
15956  CalFile.write('<0.0000, ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHAI02p5Raw) + '>\n')
15957  CalFile.write('<' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHAActSrI) + ', ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHAISr5vRaw) + '>\n')
15958  # CalFile.write('<' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHAISr0vRaw) + ', ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHAActSnkI) + '>\n')
15959  CalFile.write('<' + '{0:.4f}'.format(-CHAActSrI) + ', ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(-CHAISr5vRaw) + '>\n')
15960  CalFile.write('<>\n')
15961  CalFile.write('\n')
15962  #

15964  CalFile.write('</>\n')
15965  CalFile.write('<0.0000, ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHAF0vRaw) + '>\n')
15966  CalFile.write('<4.5000, ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHAF25V) + '>\n')
15967  CalFile.write('<>\n')
15968  CalFile.write('\n')
15969  #

15971  CalFile.write('</>\n')
15972  CalFile.write('<0.0000, ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHAISr0iRaw) + '>\n')
15973  CalFile.write('<0.045, ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHASrI100Act) + '>\n')
15974  CalFile.write('<-0.0450, ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHASrIN45Act) + '>\n')
15975  CalFile.write('<>\n')
15976  CalFile.write('\n')

15979  CalFile.write('</>\n')
15980  CalFile.write('<0.0000, ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHBGndRaw) + '>\n')
15981  CalFile.write('<' + '{0:.4f}'.format(AD584act) + ', ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHB584Raw) + '>\n')
15982  CalFile.write('<>\n')
15983  CalFile.write('\n')

15989  # CalFile.write('<' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHBISr0vRaw) + ', ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHBActSnkI) + '>\n')
15990  CalFile.write('<' + '{0:.4f}'.format(-CHBActSrI) + ', ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(-CHBISr5vRaw) + '>\n')
15991  CalFile.write('<>\n')
15992  CalFile.write('\n')

15997  CalFile.write('<4.5000, ' + '{0:.4f}'.format(CHAF25V) + '>\n')
15998  CalFile.write('<>\n')
15999  CalFile.write('\n')
16000  #

16114 def SPIShiftOut(DValue):
16115  global devx, PIO_0, PIO_1, PIO_2, PIO_3
16116 
16117  binstr = bin(DValue)
16118  binlen = len(binstr)
16119  datastr = binstr[2:binlen]
16120  datalen = len(datastr)
16121  if datalen < 16:
16122  datastr = str.rjust(datastr , 16 , '0')
16123  datalen = len(datastr)
16124  i = 1
16125  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x50, PIO_0, 0, 0, 0, 100) # fsync to 0
16126  while i < datalen+1:
16127  # sending 0x50 = set to 0, 0x51 = set to 1
16128  D1code = 0x50 + int(datastr[i-1])
16129  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, D1code, PIO_1, 0, 0, 0, 100) # data bit
16130  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, PIO_3, 0, 0, 0, 100) # sclk to 1
16131  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x50, PIO_3, 0, 0, 0, 100) # sclk to 0
16132  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, PIO_3, 0, 0, 0, 100) # sclk to 1
16133  i = i + 1
16134  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, PIO_0, 0, 0, 0, 100) # fsync to 1
16135 #
16136 def BSendMG():
16137  global MinigenFclk, MinigenFout, MinigenMode
16138  global Two28
16139 
16140  DValue = 8192 + MinigenMode.get()
16141  SPIShiftOut(DValue)
16142  try:
16143  fout = float(eval(MinigenFout.get()))
16144  except:
16145  MinigenFout.delete(0,"end")
16146  MinigenFout.insert(0,100)
16147  try:
16148  mclk = float(eval(MinigenFclk.get()))*1000000 # convert from MHz to Hz
16149  except:
16150  MingenFclk.delete(0,"end")
16151  MinigenFclk.insert(0,16)
16152  Freg = int((fout*Two28)/mclk)
16153  Foutstr = bin(Freg)
16154  Foutlen = len(Foutstr)
16155  datastr = Foutstr[2:Foutlen]
16156  datalen = len(datastr)
16157  if datalen < 28:
16158  datastr = str.rjust(datastr , 28 , '0')
16159  datalen = len(datastr)
16160  Fmsb = '0b01' + datastr[0:14]
16161  Flsb = '0b01' + datastr[14:]
16162  FValue = int(eval(Flsb))
16163  SPIShiftOut(FValue)
16164  FValue = int(eval(Fmsb))
16165  SPIShiftOut(FValue)

16217 def DA1ShiftOut(D1Value, D2Value):
16218  global devx
16219  global PIO_0, PIO_1, PIO_2, PIO_3
16220 
16221  binstr = bin(D1Value)
16222  binlen = len(binstr)
16223  data1str = binstr[2:binlen]
16224  datalen = len(data1str)
16225  if datalen < 16:
16226  data1str = str.rjust(data1str , 16 , '0')
16227  datalen = len(data1str)
16228  #
16229  binstr = bin(D2Value)
16230  binlen = len(binstr)
16231  data2str = binstr[2:binlen]
16232  datalen = len(data2str)
16233  if datalen < 16:
16234  data2str = str.rjust(data2str , 16 , '0')
16235  datalen = len(data2str)
16236  # sync --> PIO 0
16237  # D0 --> PIO 1
16238  # D1 --> PIO 2
16239  # SCLK --> PIO 3
16240  i = 1
16241 #
16242  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x50, 0, 0, 0, 0, 100) # sync to 0
16243  while i < datalen+1:
16244  # sending 0x50 = set to 0, 0x51 = set to 1
16245  D1code = 0x50 + int(data1str[i-1])
16246  D2code = 0x50 + int(data2str[i-1])
16247  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, D1code, PIO_1, 0, 0, 0, 100) # data 0 bit
16248  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, D2code, PIO_2, 0, 0, 0, 100) # data 1 bit
16249  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, PIO_3, 0, 0, 0, 100) # sclk to 1
16250  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x50, PIO_3, 0, 0, 0, 100) # sclk to 0
16251  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, PIO_3, 0, 0, 0, 100) # sclk to 1
16252  i = i + 1
16253  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, PIO_0, 0, 0, 0, 100) # sync to 1
16254  #
16255 def BSendDA1():
16256  global DAC1Entry, DAC2Entry, DAC3Entry, DAC4Entry, REFEntry
16257 
16258  try:
16259  RefValue = float(eval(REFEntry.get()))
16260  except:
16261  RefValue = 3.3
16262  try:
16263  D1Value = float(eval(DAC1Entry.get()))
16264  except:
16265  D1Value = 0.0129
16266  D1Code = int((D1Value/RefValue)*255)
16267  if D1Code > 255:
16268  D1Code = 255
16269  D1Code = D1Code + 0x2000
16270  try:
16271  D2Value = float(eval(DAC2Entry.get()))
16272  except:
16273  D2Value = 0.0129
16274  D2Code = int((D2Value/RefValue)*255)
16275  if D2Code > 255:
16276  D2Code = 255
16277  D2Code = D2Code + 0x2400
16278  try:
16279  D3Value = float(eval(DAC3Entry.get()))
16280  except:
16281  D3Value = 0.0129
16282  D3Code = int((D3Value/RefValue)*255)
16283  if D3Code > 255:
16284  D3Code = 255
16285  D3Code = D3Code + 0x2000
16286  try:
16287  D4Value = float(eval(DAC4Entry.get()))
16288  except:
16289  D4Value = 0.0129
16290  D4Code = int((D4Value/RefValue)*255)
16291  if D4Code > 255:
16292  D4Code = 255
16293  D4Code = D4Code + 0x2400
16294  #
16295  DA1ShiftOut(D1Code, D3Code)
16296  DA1ShiftOut(D2Code, D4Code)

16354 def DigPotShiftOut(DValue):
16355  global devx, SingleDualPot
16356  global PIO_0, PIO_1, PIO_2, PIO_3
16357 
16358  binstr = bin(DValue)
16359  binlen = len(binstr)
16360  datastr = binstr[2:binlen]
16361  datalen = len(datastr)
16362  if SingleDualPot.get() == 0: # send 10 bits of data
16363  if datalen < 10:
16364  datastr = str.rjust(datastr , 10 , '0')
16365  datalen = len(datastr)
16366  if SingleDualPot.get() == 1: # send 8 bits of data
16367  if datalen < 8:
16368  datastr = str.rjust(datastr , 8 , '0')
16369  datalen = len(datastr)
16370  if SingleDualPot.get() == 2: # send 8 bits of data
16371  if datalen < 8:
16372  datastr = str.rjust(datastr , 8 , '0')
16373  datalen = len(datastr)
16374  i = 1
16375  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x50, PIO_3, 0, 0, 0, 100) # clock to 0
16376  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x50, PIO_0, 0, 0, 0, 100) # CS to 0
16377  while i < datalen+1:
16378  # CS --> PIO 0
16379  # D0 --> PIO 1
16380  # D1 --> PIO 2
16381  # SCLK --> PIO 3
16382  D1code = 0x50 + int(datastr[i-1])
16383  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, D1code, PIO_1, 0, 0, 0, 100) # data bit
16384  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, PIO_3, 0, 0, 0, 100) # clock to 1
16385  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x50, PIO_3, 0, 0, 0, 100) # clock to 0
16386  i = i + 1
16387  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, 0x51, 0, 0, 0, 0, 100) # CS to 1
16388  #
16389 def DigPotSend(Temp):
16390  global DigPot1, DigPot2, DigPot3, DigPot4, SendPot1, SendPot2, SendPot3, SendPot4
16391  global SingleDualPot
16392 
16393  if SingleDualPot.get() == 0 or SingleDualPot.get() == 1:
16394  NumTaps = 255
16395  if SingleDualPot.get() == 2:
16396  NumTaps = 63
16397  try:
16398  DValue1 = DigPot1.get()
16399  if DValue1 > NumTaps:
16400  DValue1 = NumTaps
16401  except:
16402  DValue1 = 0
16403  try:
16404  DValue2 = DigPot2.get()
16405  if DValue2 > NumTaps:
16406  DValue2 = NumTaps
16407  except:
16408  DValue2 = 0
16409  try:
16410  DValue3 = DigPot3.get()
16411  if DValue3 > NumTaps:
16412  DValue3 = NumTaps
16413  except:
16414  DValue3 = 0
16415  try:
16416  DValue4 = DigPot4.get()
16417  if DValue4 > NumTaps:
16418  DValue4 = NumTaps
16419  except:
16420  DValue4 = 0
16421  if SendPot1.get() > 0:
16422  DigPotShiftOut(DValue1)
16423  if SendPot2.get() > 0:
16424  DigPotShiftOut(DValue2+NumTaps+1)
16425  if SendPot3.get() > 0:
16426  DigPotShiftOut(DValue3+2*(NumTaps+1))
16427  if SendPot4.get() > 0:
16428  DigPotShiftOut(DValue4+3*(NumTaps+1))

16503 def BSendGS():
16504  global serialwindow, GenericSerialStatus, SCLKPort, SDATAPort, SLATCHPort, SLatchPhase, SClockPhase
16505  global NumBitsEntry, DataBitsEntry, devx, SerDirection, DValue, NumBits, AD5626SerialStatus, AD5626Entry
16506 
16507  if AD5626SerialStatus.get() == 0:
16508  try:
16509  DValue = int(eval(DataBitsEntry.get()))
16510  if DValue < 0:
16511  DValue = 0
16512  except:
16513  DValue = 0
16514  try:
16515  NumBits = int(NumBitsEntry.get())
16516  if NumBits < 1:
16517  NumBits = 1
16518  except:
16519  NumBits = 8
16520  else:
16521  try:
16522  DValue = int(eval(AD5626Entry.get())*1000)
16523  if DValue < 0:
16524  DValue = 0
16525  AD5626Entry.delete(0,"end")
16526  AD5626Entry.insert(0,'0.000')
16527  if DValue > 4095:
16528  DValue = 4095
16529  AD5626Entry.delete(0,"end")
16530  AD5626Entry.insert(0,DValue/1000.0)
16531  except:
16532  DValue = 0
16533  AD5626Entry.delete(0,"end")
16534  AD5626Entry.insert(0,'0.000')
16535  NumBits = 12
16536  # print DValue
16537  binstr = bin(DValue)
16538  binlen = len(binstr)
16539  datastr = binstr[2:binlen]
16540  datalen = len(datastr)
16541  if datalen < NumBits:
16542  datastr = str.rjust(datastr , NumBits , '0')
16543  datalen = len(datastr)
16544  if SLatchPhase.get() == 0:
16545  LatchInt = 0x50
16546  LatchEnd = 0x51
16547  else:
16548  LatchInt = 0x51
16549  LatchEnd = 0x50
16550  if AD5626SerialStatus.get() > 0:
16551  LatchInt = 0x51
16552  LatchEnd = 0x50
16553  if SClockPhase.get() == 0:
16554  ClockInt = 0x50
16555  ClockEnd = 0x51
16556  else:
16557  ClockInt = 0x51
16558  ClockEnd = 0x50
16559  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, ClockInt, SCLKPort.get(), 0, 0, 0, 100) # clock to start value
16560  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, LatchInt, SLATCHPort.get(), 0, 0, 0, 100) # CS to start value
16561  i = 1
16562  while i < datalen+1:
16563  if SerDirection.get() == 1: # for MSB first
16564  D1code = 0x50 + int(datastr[datalen-i]) # 0x50 = set to 0, 0x51 = set to 1
16565  else:
16566  D1code = 0x50 + int(datastr[i-1]) # for LSB first
16567  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, D1code, SDATAPort.get(), 0, 0, 0, 100) # data bit
16568  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, ClockEnd, SCLKPort.get(), 0, 0, 0, 100) # clock to end value
16569  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, ClockInt, SCLKPort.get(), 0, 0, 0, 100) # clock to start value
16570  i = i + 1
16571  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, ClockEnd, SCLKPort.get(), 0, 0, 0, 100) # clock to end value
16572  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, LatchEnd, SLATCHPort.get(), 0, 0, 0, 100) # CS to end value
16573  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, LatchInt, SLATCHPort.get(), 0, 0, 0, 100) # CS to start value
16574  devx.ctrl_transfer(0x40, LatchEnd, SLATCHPort.get(), 0, 0, 0, 100) # CS to end value
16575 #

16800 def BLoadDFiltA():
16801  global DFiltACoef, digfltwindow, DifFiltALength, DifFiltAFile
16802 
16803 # Read values from CVS file
16804  filename = askopenfilename(defaultextension = ".csv", filetypes=[("CSV files", "*.csv")], parent=digfltwindow)
16805  try:
16806  CSVFile = open(filename)
16807  csv_f = csv.reader(CSVFile)
16808  except:
16809  showwarning("WARNING","No such file found or wrong format!", parent=digfltwindow)
16810  return
16811  DFiltACoef = []
16812 
16813  for row in csv_f:
16814  try:
16815  DFiltACoef.append(float(row[0]))
16816  except:
16817  print 'skipping non-numeric row'
16818  DFiltACoef = numpy.array(DFiltACoef)
16819  DifFiltALength.config(text = "Length = " + str(int(len(DFiltACoef)))) # change displayed length value
16820  DifFiltAFile.config(text = "File Name, " + os.path.basename(filename)) # change displayed file name
16821  CSVFile.close()
16822 #
16823 def BDFiltAMath():
16824  global DFiltACoef, digfltwindow, DifFiltALength, DifFiltAFile, DigFilterAString
16825 
16826  TempString = DigFilterAString
16827  DigFilterAString = askstring("CH A Filter Math Formula", "Current Formula: " + DigFilterAString + "\n\nNew Formula:\n", initialvalue=DigFilterAString, parent=digfltwindow)
16828  if (DigFilterAString == None): # If Cancel pressed, then None
16829  DigFilterAString = TempString
16830  return
16831  DFiltACoef = eval(DigFilterAString)
16832  DFiltACoef = numpy.array(DFiltACoef)
16833  coefsum = numpy.sum(DFiltACoef)
16834  DFiltACoef = DFiltACoef / coefsum
16835  DifFiltALength.config(text = "Length = " + str(int(len(DFiltACoef)))) # change displayed length value
16836  DifFiltAFile.config(text = "Using Filter A formula" ) # change displayed file name
16837

16912 def BExecuteFromString(): # global VBuffA,AWGAwaveform;VBuffA=AWGAwaveform
16913  global ExecString, LastCommand
16914 
16915  try:
16916  exec( ExecString.get() )
16917  LastCommand.config(text = ExecString.get() ) # change displayed last command
16918  except:
16919  LastCommand.config(text = "Syntax Error Encountered" ) # change displayed last command
16920  return()
